04488nam a22007695i 9789814786058DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20172017si     fo  d z      eng d  a97898147860587 a10.1355/97898147860582doi  a(DE-B1597)522096  a(OCoLC)1096436809  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  asicSG 7aPOL0160002bisacsh1 aFionna, Ulla, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aInvestigating the Popularity of Surabaya's Mayor Tri Rismaharini /cUlla Fionna. 1aSingapore : bISEAS Publishing, c[2017] 4c©2017  a1 online resource (28 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tFOREWORD -- tInvestigating the Popularity of Surabaya’s Mayor Tri Rismaharini -- tInvestigating the Popularity of Surabaya’s Mayor Tri Rismaharini -- tSURABAYA: A HISTORICAL AND SOCIAL POLITICAL PROFILE -- tPUBLIC POLICIES UNDER PREVIOUS GOVERNMENTS -- tJUXTAPOSING RISMA’S POPULARITY WITH HER POLICIES -- tLIMITS AND SHAPES OF SUPPORT FOR RISMA -- tAPPENDIX A Research Design -- tAPPENDIX B Demographic Composition of Respondents (N=410) -- tAPPENDIX C0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIndonesia's decentralization and direct local elections have produced several credible popular local leaders. One of them is Surabaya's mayor, Tri Rismaharini (Risma), who gained much attention for her impressive work ethics and her commitment in improving the city. Together with new vice mayor Whisnu Sakti Buana, she was successfully re-elected for the second term in 2015. Examination on the perception and support for her policies on cleanliness, the closure of Dolly (Surabaya's main red light district) and the management of education reveals that Risma is perceived as a capable leader. However, Surabaya residents still want Risma to do more on those particular fronts. This finding signals maturing voters who are not only aware of their needs and what their government does, but also are able to push their leaders to develop their successful policies further. Risma's success in Surabaya showcases an effective combination between an electorate that is politically savvy and a bold local leader with a clear and sustained focus in the implementation of her policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aElections—Indonesia—Surabaya. 0aPolitical Process. 0aSurabaya (Indonesia)—Politics and government. 0aTri Rismaharini, 1961–. 0aWomen mayors—Indonesia—Surabaya. 4aPolitical Process. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh1 aFionna, Ulla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066298608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981478605840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814786058423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814786058.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066298-6  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK